# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a long-standing immigration law making it easier for children born out of wedlock overseas to become a u.s. citizen if their mother is a citizen is unconstitutional sex discrimination , a federal appeals court ruled thursday .
# ::alignments
(r / rule-01
      :ARG0 (g / government-organization
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Federal"
                  :op2 "Appeals"
                  :op3 "Court"))
      :ARG3 (d / discriminate-02
            :mod (s / sex)
            :domain (l / law
                  :topic (ii / immigrate-01)
                  :ARG1-of (s2 / stand-04
                        :ARG1-of (l2 / long-03))
                  :ARG0-of (m / make-02
                        :ARG1 (e / easy-05
                              :ARG1 (b / become-01
                                    :ARG1 (c / child
                                          :ARG1-of (b2 / bear-02
                                                :location (o / overseas))
                                          :ARG1-of (o2 / out-06
                                                :ARG2 (w / wedlock-01)))
                                    :ARG2 (c2 / citizen
                                          :mod (c3 / country
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "U.S.")))
                                    :condition (c4 / citizen
                                          :domain (p / person
                                                :ARG0-of (h / have-rel-role-91
                                                      :ARG1 c
                                                      :ARG2 (m2 / mother)))))
                              :ARG2-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                                    :ARG1 b
                                    :ARG3 (m3 / more)))))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday))))

            :op1 b)

                  :part-of (c2 / clubhouse
                        :poss (t2 / team
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Yankees")))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t3 / tuesday)))

      :ARG0 (o / organization
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Hong"
                  :op2 "Kong"
                  :op3 "Trade"
                  :op4 "Development"
                  :op5 "Council"))
      :ARG1 (r / rise-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / sell-01
                  :ARG0 o
                  :ARG3 (r2 / retail-01)
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :month 1))
            :ARG2 (a / and
                  :op1 (p / percentage-entity
                        :value 1
                        :prep-in (v / value))
                  :op2 (p2 / percentage-entity
                        :value 1
                        :prep-in (v2 / volume)))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :month 12
                  :mod (l / last))))

                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "Denmark"))

                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (s2 / sugar))
            :duration (t / temporal-quantity
                  :quant 5
                  :unit (y / year))
            :time (p / provide-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (s3 / support-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (p2 / person
                              :ARG0-of (f / farm-01
                                    :ARG1 (b2 / beet
                                          :consist-of (s4 / sugar))))
                        :mod (f2 / finance))
                  :ARG2 p2
                  :time (t2 / transition-01)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t3 / tuesday)))

# ::id 1945 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

                  :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01)))

                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Canada"))

                        :ARG1-of (n2 / new-01)
                        :ARG1-of (l / lead-02

                                    :ARG1-of (p / private-03))))
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :month 11)
                  :ARG1-of (e / expect-01
                        :polarity -))
            :ARG2 (e2 / edge-01
                  :ARG0 (j2 / join-up-02
                        :ARG0 (p2 / person
                              :quant (m / more))
                        :ARG1 (f / force
                              :mod (l2 / labor-01)))
                  :ARG1 (r / rate
                        :mod (e3 / employ-01
                              :polarity -)
                        :poss c3)
                  :direction (u / up)))
      :time d
      :weekday (f2 / friday))
